com.symantec.dlpx.flexresponse.action

Interface IncidentResponseAction


  • public interface IncidentResponseAction
    An action that is invoked to respond to an incident. Instances are created by IncidentResponseActionFactory.newIncidentResponseAction().

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ActionResult execute(Incident incident, ConfigurationParameters parameters)
      Execute an action.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        ActionResult execute(Incident incident,
                     ConfigurationParameters parameters)
              throws UnsupportedIncidentTypeException,
                     java.lang.InterruptedException
        Execute an action. This method is called when a user runs this plug-in in response to an incident.
        Parameters:
        incident - Describes the incident that the user selected for this incident response.
        parameters - Additional configuration parameters for this response.
        Returns:
        The result of executing this action. An ActionResult is created using an ActionResultBuilder. This cannot be null.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedIncidentTypeException - if the incident is of a type that is unsupported by this action.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - if this action gets interrupted by the framework it should throw an InterruptedException.
        See Also:
        ActionResultBuilder, Plugin
